        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.7-10_0001" />
                <note type="curatorial">10. Bowen letter</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                <address><addrLine>Skyrim Farm,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Route 6,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Columbia, Mo.</addrLine></address>
                
                <date>Jan. 15, '55</date>
                    </dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Dr. Bowen:</salute>
                </opener>
                
                <p>Good to hear from you! Yes, that poem has had some adventures in its 30 years of life! I've even seen it with other names than mine attached &#8212; and feel flattered. One very old man came to think he wrote it himself. A sourdough in Alaska declared it saved his life &#8212; etc. etc.</p>

<p>Use the second version.</p>
<p>"Let me <hi rend="underline">lie</hi>" must be "Let me 
                    <hi rend="underline">die</hi>."</p>
<p>"Soul-house" hyphenated.</p>
<p>"Time-swept" is horrible! Make it "<hi rend="underline">"tune</hi>-swept."</p>
                
                <p>Things go very well at the University. My <hi rend="underline">Epic America</hi> course continues to be popular and classes grow larger and larger
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.7-10_0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    in spite of stiff requirements. I teach two writing courses also. Lots of fun!</p>
                
                <p>It seems I'm to read poetry at the Michigan State College Speech Conference, June 25-26. Perhaps I shall see you.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Kindest thoughts</salute>
                <signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.20.7-10_0003"/>
                <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
<div1 type="attachment">
                <p>From <hi rend="caps">THE QUEST</hi> (1928), page 50:</p>
                <lg>
                <head>LET ME LIVE OUT MY YEARS</head>
                
                <lg><l>Let me live out my years in heat of blood!</l>
                <note type="authorial">Correct</note>  <l>Let me die drunken with the dreamer's wine!</l>
                <l>Let me not see this soul-house built of mud</l>
                <l>Go toppling to the dust--a vacant shrine!</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>Let me go quickly like a candle light</l>
                <l>Snuffed out just at the heyday of its glow!</l>
                <l>Give me high noon--and let it then be night!</l>
                <l>Thus would I go.</l></lg>
                
                <lg><l>And grant me, when I face the grisly Thing,</l>
                <l><hi rend="underline">One haughty cry to pierce the gray Perhaps!</hi></l>
<l>Let me be as a <hi rend="underline">tune</hi>-swept fiddlestring</l>
                <l>That feels the Master Melody--and snaps!</l></lg>
                </lg>
                
                
                <p>From Argus Tresidder, <hi rend="caps">READING TO OTHERS</hi>, Scott, Foresman, 1940, p. 348 (acknowledgement to Macmillan and <hi rend="caps">THE QUEST</hi>):</p>
                
                <lg><l>Let me live out my years in heat of blood!</l>
                <note type="authorial">Misprint!</note>      <l>Let me lie drunken with the dreamer's wine!</l>
                <l>Let me not see this soul house built of mud</l>
                <l>Go toppling to the dust--a vacant shrine.</l>
                
                <l>Let me go quickly like a candle light</l>
                <l>Snuffed out just at the heyday of its glow.</l>
                <l>Give me high noon--and let it then be night!</l>
                <l>Thus would I go.</l>
                
                <l>And grant me, when I face the grisly Thing,</l>
                <l><hi rend="underline">My song may trumpet down the grey Perhaps</hi>.</l>
                <note type="authorial">Correct</note>  <l>O let me be a time-swept fiddle string</l>
                <l>That feels the Master-Melody--and snaps.</l></lg>
                
                <note type="authorial">This is a misprint &#8212; very bad! Should be <hi rend="underline">TUNE</hi>.</note>
                <note type="authorial">Keep second version with indicated corrections of misprints.</note>
            </div1>
